{
  "texts": [
    "One prominent line of work explores debate-based interactions.",
    "The MAD framework [66] introduces an asymmetric role design, where agents take on distinct roles such as debater and judge to evaluate arguments.",
    "In contrast, Liang et al. [40] propose a symmetric debate structure, enabling agents to engage in equal-status dialogues for collective decision-making.",
    "These paradigms have been successfully applied to tasks including machine translation and mathematical reasoning, yielding improved outcomes.",
    "Further refinements, such as ReConcile [78], leverage weighted voting across heterogeneous LLMs to enhance decision quality."
  ]
}